# Our App Infrastructure

Let's revisit your app architecture.

```text
                 User

                   │

                   ▼

          📱 Flutter Mobile App

                   │

            Internet (HTTPS)

                   │

                   ▼

          🌐 FastAPI Backend

      ┌────────┼────────┐

      ▼        ▼        ▼

 PostgreSQL   S3      OCR

 Database   Storage   Service

                   │

                   ▼

               OpenAI API
```

Every component has one responsibility.

---

# Step 1 – Mobile App

The Flutter app is installed on the user's phone.

Users download it from:

* Google Play Store (Android)
* Apple App Store (iPhone)

The app itself does not store all the reports permanently.

Instead, it requests data from the backend.

---

# Step 2 – Backend Server

Your FastAPI backend runs on a cloud server.

Its job is to:

* Receive requests
* Verify login
* Save reports
* Call OCR
* Call AI
* Send responses

Think of it as the **brain** of your application.

---

# Step 3 – Database

Your PostgreSQL database also runs in the cloud.

It stores:

* User accounts
* Report information
* Blood test values
* AI summaries

The backend talks to the database.

Users never access the database directly.

---

# Step 4 – File Storage

PDFs and images are stored separately.

Example:

```text
Cloud Storage

↓

Report1.pdf

↓

Report2.pdf

↓

Report3.pdf
```

This keeps the database fast and organized.

---

# Step 5 – OCR Service

When a report is uploaded:

```text
PDF

↓

OCR

↓

Extracted Text
```

The backend sends the file to OCR and receives structured text back.

---

# Step 6 – AI

After OCR is complete:

```text
Blood Values

↓

OpenAI

↓

Plain Language Explanation
```

The AI never talks directly to the user's phone.

Everything goes through your backend.

---

# Step 7 – Internet

Every request travels over the internet.

Example:

```text
Phone

↓

HTTPS

↓

Backend
```

HTTPS keeps the communication encrypted and secure.

---

